12/08/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The start of the holy month of Ramadan was marked on Wednesday (August 11th) by the head of the Muslim Community in Albania, Selim Muca.
"This month will enrich the souls and minds of believers," he said in an address to all Muslims in the country.
"Wherever you are inside and outside Albania, the month of Ramadan has come to revive the hope of Muslim believers and make them stronger in the devotion towards God," he added.
The Muslim community has organised TV programmes, religious discussions in TV studios, and broadcasts of Muslim ceremonies during the month.
Around 70% of all Albanians are Muslim.
(Top News, Balkan Web, Klan - 11/08/10)
